The paper proposes a motion planning system for autonomous quadrotors, which involves robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), control systems (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of sliding-windowed local perception and re-planning, which is a common technique in robotics and control systems. Therefore, cs.RO is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI and cs.CV. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG. Finally, the paper discusses control systems and kinematics, which could fall under cs.SY.
